  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2004-03-02",
    "date": "2004-07-28T16:52:52Z",
    "text": "Commission on American Jobs Act - Directs the Secretary of Commerce to establish a Commission on American Jobs. Requires the Commission to: (1) collect data on the outsourcing of jobs by specified types of companies of interest; (2) study such outsourcing's causes; (3) propose prevention measures; and (4) report to specified congressional committees.\n\nRequires such companies to report outsourcing data annually to the Commission."
  },
